The innerHTML property is a common tool in web development used to get or set the HTML content inside a specific element. 
---------------------

Core Functionality
Getting Content: It returns the internal HTML or XML markup of an element as a string, including all tags, text, and formatting.
=====================================
Setting Content: When you assign a string to innerHTML, it completely replaces the existing content of that element with the new HTML markup you provided. 
====================================
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Basic example:
// Selecting an element by its ID
const element = document.getElementById("myDiv");

// Reading the content
console.log(element.innerHTML); 

// Changing the content
element.innerHTML = "<strong>New content!</strong>";
